parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling at highway speeds can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning while driving at high speeds
often accompanied by an "Engine Stalled" message on the instrument panel. The vehicle may coast to the side of the road
and the engine may restart after turning off and back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of timing chain tensioners can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: The timing chain tensioners break or crack
leading to engine damage and potential stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Stalling due to Faulty Engine Relays
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: and may be accompanied by an "Engine Stalled" message on the instrument panel. The stalling may occur repeatedly
even after replacement of engine relays.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the O-ring inside the transmission can cause the transmission to fail, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The Nakasil engine issues can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the serpentine belt tensioner can cause the belt to slip, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the throttle body can cause the accelerator to suddenly fail to respond while driving, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents, especially on high-speed roads with limited emergency lanes.
symptoms: Sudden loss of acceleration while driving on the freeway
usually 10 minutes after a cold start

with no warning indicators; the accelerator pedal fails to respond; the vehicle can only be stopped by merging to the side of the road using momentum; the "Engine Failed" indicator and red engine light appear after stopping and putting the car in park.
